title: ICE: `assertion failed: `(left matches right)`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: S-has-mcve
labels.description: A Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example has been found for this issue

labels.name: requires-debug-assertions
labels.description: This issue requires debug-assertions in some way

body:
### Code ```Rust pub trait TraitWAssocConst { const A: usize; } fn foo>() {} fn main<>() { foo::(); } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` 4e463012580415a932ae4fc255aff45982c70369 ``` ### Error output ``` error[E0658]: associated const equality is incomplete --> treereduce.out:5:31 | 5 | fn foo>() {} | ^^^^ | = note: see issue #92827 for more information = help: add `#![feature(associated_const_equality)]` to the crate attributes to enable warning: trait objects without an explicit `dyn` are deprecated --> treereduce.out:9:9 | 9 | foo::(); | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ | = warning: this is accepted in the current edition (Rust 2015) but is a hard error in Rust 2021! = note: for more information, see = note: `#[warn(bare_trait_objects)]` on by default help: use `dyn` | 9 | foo::(); | +++ ```
